      "updated": 1782154985276,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Composite Design Pattern :-",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Composite Design Pattern :-",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "d4znoTC-yOgbwT_tL5ZGF",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 313.2440241673977,
      "y": 10.441477104717137,
      "width": 835.539306640625,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2002339093,
      "version": 171,
      "versionNonce": 494517312,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782154985276,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "THis are not generic but simple use case specific means solves specific problem onnly. \n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "THis are not generic but simple use case specific means solves specific problem onnly. \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "SGewCKljW1zEQTxb4Ye7h",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 308.1884727636892,
      "y": 79.20798526892986,
      "width": 974.4393310546875,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a5",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 82925128,
      "version": 328,
      "versionNonce": 2004366400,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782154985276,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Composite meanss :- Tree like hierarchy, it is used for tree like hierarchy, like there are going to be \nnodes, leafs, parent child relation, \nComposite basically means non leaf nodes in the tree - this is MMIMP",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Composite meanss :- Tree like hierarchy, it is used for tree like hierarchy, like there are going to be \nnodes, leafs, parent child relation, \nComposite basically means non leaf nodes in the tree - this is MMIMP",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dIFp6KeEXjGnXkNc-Gcfr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 324.41065429580715,
      "y": 192.20798526892992,
      "width": 954.4993896484375,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2006891848,
      "version": 402,
      "versionNonce": 2062003264,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782154985276,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Eg. File systems, root has multiple folders and files , in the folders there are going to be a files, \nthis files are not gonna have more files hence all the files are leaf nodes, while the folders can \nhave the multiple folders and files both hence it is composite simple!!!",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Eg. File systems, root has multiple folders and files , in the folders there are going to be a files, \nthis files are not gonna have more files hence all the files are leaf nodes, while the folders can \nhave the multiple folders and files both hence it is composite simple!!!",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6AvSiceescLzyGDi83Q9I",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 310.56102178329695,
      "y": 320.79530144540036,
      "width": 972.6746251723345,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1512647224,
      "version": 424,
      "versionNonce": 598093760,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782154992443,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Eg. All the tree like problems like , shoping cart(shoping cart is also a box), product and boxes,\nboxes ccan have other boxes\nand product is product cant have other boxes, hence boxes are like composite while product is like\nfiles simple \nfiles and leaf nodes simple!!, Box is like folder simple!!!",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Eg. All the tree like problems like , shoping cart(shoping cart is also a box), product and boxes, boxes ccan have other boxes\nand product is product cant have other boxes, hence boxes are like composite while product is like files simple \nfiles and leaf nodes simple!!, Box is like folder simple!!!",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "XbAdqSK0e0Ip3JWAjm56U",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 332.14426875786785,
      "y": 1004.069504876773,
      "width": 1082.5349035844538,
      "height": 116.00000000000003,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aA",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 863583816,
      "version": 726,
      "versionNonce": 642062272,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782155073914,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Here we can implement ls command or calculate total size of root folder or calculate total cost\nin shoping cart then we need to recursively travel all the composite to get the total untill we\nhave traversed all products or files or folders using recrusion simple just like the tree traversal\nsimple!!!",
      "fontSize": 23.200000000000006,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Here we can implement ls command or calculate total size of root folder or calculate total cost in shoping cart then we need to recursively travel all the composite to get the total untill we have traversed all products or files or folders using recrusion simple just like the tree traversal simple!!!",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "XE4fDkaXizMuyi7zA4_Vz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 256.6680338282267,
      "y": 1170.520984170958,
      "width": 1414.500050264246,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aB",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1987613294,
      "version": 1036,
      "versionNonce": 405161920,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782155482146,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The main issue that composite patterns solve is to avoid the if else issue like if its box do this else do this, we dont do '\nthat here we simple treat the both exectly the same simple!!!\nBasicllly Both compoite and leaf will be node with same methods it depends on how we want to implement this methods, in composite we will use \nrecurson tocall or we use for loops if we have the list of child nodes, in leaf we also have all methods but instead of for loop or recursion we\nwill \nsimple return 0 or base value return kardende like price or file storage etc simple",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The main issue that composite patterns solve is to avoid the if else issue like if its box do this else do this, we dont do '\nthat here we simple treat the both exectly the same simple!!!\nBasicllly Both compoite and leaf will be node with same methods it depends on how we want to implement this methods, in composite we will use \nrecurson tocall or we use for loops if we have the list of child nodes, in leaf we also have all methods but instead of for loop or recursion we will \nsimple return 0 or base value return kardende like price or file storage etc simple",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
